reason.tex:
%text
The slope $m$ will be as follows  

%
\begin{align}
m &= \left[\frac{dy}{dx}\right]_{t=\frac\pi{4}} = \left[\frac{dy / dt}{dx / dt}\right]_{t=\frac\pi{4}} \\
&= \left[\dfrac{-2\sin 2t}{3\cos 3t}\right]_{t=\frac\pi{4}} = \dfrac{-2\times 1}{3\times -\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}} \\
&= \frac{2\sqrt{2}}{3} 
\end{align}

%text We know the slope of the tangent $(m)$ and the one point it passes through $A$\newline
Hence, the equation is simply
\begin{align} \dfrac{y - y_A}{x - x_A} &= m \implies \dfrac{y - 0}{\left( x-\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\right)} = \dfrac{2\sqrt{2}}{3} \\ \text{or } 3y &= 2\sqrt{2}\cdot\left( x - \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\right) = 2\sqrt{2}x - 2 \end{align}
